# nbstripout discipline (per `.pre-commit-config.yaml` nbstripout hook):
#
# Default: nbstripout strips output cells from .ipynb at commit time.
#
# v1.2.8 exception: `notebooks/*.ipynb` are committed WITH outputs frozen
# per /exploring-options batch 9 Q2 lock ("pre-rendered + frozen output
# cells"). Companion scripts live under notebooks/_jupytext/. These notebooks
# are reviewer-display artifacts rendered by Quarto + visible on the live site;
# operators regenerate them via `make notebooks`. CI does NOT re-execute them.
# This preserves the disclosed Option-2 strategy from v1.0.7; see ADR-053 +
# ADR-054 reading-guide governance.
notebooks/*.ipynb -nbstripout
